INNER TURF FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE SEPTEMBER 28, 2022. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: ERASMO'S GIRL was bumped on the break, settled near the rear in the beginning, nudged to get involved more entering the backstretch, came under a ride three furlongs from the wire, was urged left handed with five sixteenths to go to rally three wide with a quarter mile to run, swung outside widest in the five path looking the main threat turning for home and pulled away easily in the final sixteenth. PHIL IN ECHO stumbled, breaking outwards at the start, travelled on the rail in midfield through the first turn, took closer order inside to be part of the tracking trio at the half, waited on the fence through the far turn, slipped up the rail at the quarter pole but was no match for the winner but bested the rest comfortably in the end. TEXT ME UP was brushed inside being pushed out slightly on the break, kept a close eye while three deep outside foes watching the loose speed horse down the back straight, closed in to bid three wide three eighths from the finish, had a chance in the three path battling up front straightening out for the drive, could not find another gear late and faded while holding for third at the finish. A GAL FOR T J tracked the frontrunner two wide on the first turn, was content sitting back off the loose pacesetter down the backstretch, bid between horses in the two path three furlongs from home, could not quicken with runners midway on the far turn, lost action inside the quarter pole and faded in upper stretch. FORESTERS PRINCESS was eager early clearing to the lead on the rail setting a brisk pace into the first turn, continued up front unchallenged down the backside posting strong fractions at the half, was headed by foes with three eighths to run, roused maintaining position, mildly spurted away at the quarter pole, was collared on each side in upper stretch and yielded. ABSOLUTE JEWEL was unhurried trailing the field in the early stages, began to gather momentum lengthening stride at the three furlong marker inside, closed in quickly on the tiring leaders between rivals at the quarter pole, clipped heels, fell and walked off. STEWARDS GENERAL INQUIRY AT THE QUARTER POLE RESULTED IN NO CHANGE

CLOUD STORAGE took this field down the backside, maintained a slim advantage through the turn, was collared by the winner outside at the top of the lane, offered little resistance and retreated on the fence in mid-stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCKLAND EXPRESS reared up leaving the gate, saved ground around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack between horses for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend, switched to the outside to launch a bid nearing the eighth pole and got up for the win late. MISTER MESEEKS saved ground early, trailed the field up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the second turn, took over the lead in midstretch and was caught after drifting out late. PERFECT PLAY bumped with the horse to her inside at the break, saved ground around the first bend, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, came around the far turn in the four path and improved position late, racing into traffic late and being forced to steady near the wire when MISTER MESEEKS drifted out. BILL NEEDLE tracked the leaders on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far bend still in the three path, raced in tight quarters entering the stretch and kept on to the wire. ROBITAILLE saved ground early, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the four path and was outkicked from there. QUIET REBEL raced off the pace in the three path around the first turn and up the backstretch, began a bid approaching the half mile pole, led the field from the two path around the second turn and faded in the final furlong. HIP TO YOUR TRICKS raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the pace setters on the inside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and tired in the lane. THE RIDER OF HORSE EIGHT, PERFECT PLAY, CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST BOTH HORSE THREE, MISTER MESEEKS AND HORSE FOUR, ROCKLAND EMPRESS, CITING INTERFERENCE NEAR THE WIRE.
